## Description

This repository contains application implementation using Compose, MVVM, Clean Architecture, Hilt, Firebase Realtime Database, Firebase Authentication



## To run it

1. Get a [Maps API key][api-key]
2. Create a file in the root directory named `local.properties` with a single line that looks like this, replacing YOUR_KEY with the key from step 1: `GOOGLE_API_KEY=YOUR_KEY`
3. Build and run



## Functionality

Main Screen contains Google Map and "Current Location" button.
By clicking on "Current Location" moves the map to the user's location.
A long press on the map shows Firebase Authentication. After successful authorization, a new screen is displayed where the user can add a picture, name, description and save the location.
The saved locations are then displayed on the map by placing markers on the corresponding locations.
If user clicks on marker it redirect him to screen with details for this location. These details can be edited and updated. Also selected location can be deleted.
This data is stored in the Firebase Realtime database.
The program contains a screen where all the saved places are shown in the form of a list.
The user has the option to change the appearance of this list by clicking the button in the lower left corner
List screen have pagination with 10 items per page.
